# Test 11: Deep negation chain (4 levels)
# Regression test for the v1.1/v1.1.1/v1.1.2 stratification bugs:
#   - a copy-rule (P :- P_impl_N) must never run in an earlier stratum than
#     the impl rule it copies from (v1.1.1: it did, so P stayed empty forever)
#   - removing stratification entirely and evaluating all rules in one flat,
#     unordered fixpoint is not a fix: with no fact retraction, a rule that
#     negates a predicate which is not yet fully computed can permanently
#     commit a wrong fact (v1.2 fell into exactly this)
#   - a variable bound by a positive atom and also checked in a negative
#     atom must unify correctly, not be rejected outright (v1.1.2 regression)
#
# a(x) is a base fact. b negates a, c negates b, d negates c: this forces
# 4 distinct strata and the results must alternate TRUE/FALSE/TRUE/FALSE.

relation base(x)

derive a(x) from base(x)
derive b(x) from base(x), not a(x)
derive c(x) from base(x), not b(x)
derive d(x) from base(x), not c(x)

input {
    base(k1)
}

query a(k1)
query b(k1)
query c(k1)
query d(k1)
